&lt;Bralorne Resources Ltd> saidit reached agreement in principle with its long term lendersfor a debt rescheduling plan.    When the agreements are finalized, Bralorne's debtstructure will be modified so that debt servicing requirementsmatch available cash flow for each of the next three years.    During that period, principal payments will be deferred, ifnecessary, and interest will be capitalized on a portion of thelong term debt, it said.    Bralorne said it expects these agreements will enable thecompany to operate within its cash flows and provide a stablefinancial environment until the energy industry recovers. Reuter&#3;